## Sprint 3: Transform & Selection Polish

> **Goal**: Make transform and selection feel like real editing tools, not hidden features.
> **Duration**: ~1 week
> **Dependencies**: None — current codebase is ready.

### 3A — Interactive Transform Handles on Canvas (§52)

#### [MODIFY] [transform.rs](file:///d:/project/ARTY/src/tools/transform.rs)

Currently `TransformState` has the affine math but is entirely `#[allow(dead_code)]`. Wire it up:

- Add `TransformHandle` enum: `TopLeft`, `Top`, `TopRight`, `Left`, `Center`, `Right`, `BottomLeft`, `Bottom`, `BottomRight`, `Rotation`
- Add `dragging_handle: Option<TransformHandle>` to `TransformState`
- Add `drag_start_world: (f32, f32)` and `initial_matrix: [f32; 6]` for tracking
- Add `bounding_rect() -> (f32, f32, f32, f32)` computed from source snapshot extents
- Implement `hit_test_handle(world_pos) -> Option<TransformHandle>` with 8px screen-space radius
- Implement `update_drag(handle, world_delta, shift_held, alt_held)`:
  - Corner handles → scale both axes (Shift = proportional)
  - Edge handles → scale one axis
  - Center → translate
  - Rotation handle → rotate around center (above top-center, offset ~20px)

#### [MODIFY] [app.rs](file:///d:/project/ARTY/src/app.rs)

- On `ToolId::Transform` + pointer press: call `transform.hit_test_handle()`, begin drag
- On pointer drag: call `transform.update_drag()`, request repaint
- On pointer release: end drag
- On `Enter` key: call `transform.apply_transform(layer)`, push undo command, clear transform
- On `Esc` key: restore from `source_snapshot`, clear transform
- Draw transform overlay in canvas paint callback:
  - Dashed bounding box (white + black alternating for contrast)
  - 8 square handle indicators at corners/edges (6×6px screen-space)
  - Circle rotation handle above top-center
  - Numeric readouts: position, scale %, rotation °

### 3B — Marching Ants Selection Outline (§51)

#### [MODIFY] [selection.rs](file:///d:/project/ARTY/src/tools/selection.rs)

- Add `extract_selection_outline(mask: &SelectionMask) -> Vec<(f32, f32, f32, f32)>` — returns line segments at edges where mask transitions from selected to unselected
- Cache outline segments; invalidate when selection changes

#### [MODIFY] [app.rs](file:///d:/project/ARTY/src/app.rs)

- Add `selection_outline_segments: Vec<(f32, f32, f32, f32)>` cache field
- Add `selection_outline_phase: f32` for animated dash offset
- Draw marching ants in canvas overlay:
  - Two-pass rendering: black solid line underneath, white dashed line on top
  - Advance phase by `4.0 * dt` each frame for animation
- Add `SelectionDisplayMode` enum: `MarchingAnts`, `MaskOverlay`, `Hidden` (per §51)
- Toggle via View menu: "Selection Display ▸ Marching Ants / Mask Overlay / Hidden"

### 3C — Selection Floating Toolbar

#### [MODIFY] [app.rs](file:///d:/project/ARTY/src/app.rs)

When selection is active, show a small floating toolbar near the selection:
- Buttons: `Grow (+)`, `Shrink (-)`, `Feather (~)`, `Invert`, `Deselect`
- Position: anchored below selection bounding box or at status bar if off-screen
- Auto-hide when no selection is active

### Verification

- [ ] Transform handles render correctly at all zoom levels and rotation
- [ ] Shift-drag corner preserves aspect ratio
- [ ] Enter applies, Esc cancels, both with undo
- [ ] Marching ants animate smoothly at 60fps
- [ ] Selection display mode toggles correctly

