## Sprint 6: Layer Mask System (§29, §55)

> **Goal**: Non-destructive layer masking, like SAI/Krita.
> **Duration**: ~1 week
> **Dependencies**: Sprint 5 (undo for mask operations).

### 6A — Data model

#### [MODIFY] [canvas.rs](file:///d:/project/ARTY/src/canvas.rs)

```rust
pub struct LayerMask {
    pub tiles: AHashMap<(i32, i32), Box<[u8; 4096]>>,
    pub enabled: bool,
    pub linked: bool,  // move mask with layer
}
```

Add `mask: Option<LayerMask>` field to `Layer`.

### 6B — Compositing integration

#### [MODIFY] [renderer.rs](file:///d:/project/ARTY/src/renderer.rs)

In `compose_layers()`, after computing layer opacity, multiply by mask value:
- Missing mask tile → treat as fully white (fully visible)
- `mask.enabled == false` → skip mask entirely
- Upload mask tiles to GPU as single-channel textures

#### [MODIFY] [shaders/blending.wgsl](file:///d:/project/ARTY/src/shaders/blending.wgsl)

Add mask texture sampler; multiply alpha by mask value before blending.

### 6C — UI integration

- Layer panel: mask icon/button per layer (add/apply/delete)
- When painting with mask selected: brush writes to mask tile data instead of color tiles
- Context menu: "Add Mask", "Apply Mask", "Delete Mask", "Invert Mask"
- Mask thumbnail in layer panel (separate from color thumbnail)

### Verification

- [ ] Painting on mask hides/reveals layer content
- [ ] Apply mask flattens mask into layer alpha
- [ ] Delete mask restores full visibility
