## Resolved Design Decisions (from /grill-me)

> [!NOTE]
> **Q1: Transform Real-time Preview Rendering**
> - **Decision**: Hybrid GPU/CPU. The real-time drag preview will be rendered at 60fps in the viewport by transforming the active layer's quad coordinates on the GPU (WGPU). The transformation will only be committed/rasterized on the CPU (using `apply_transform`) when the user hits Enter.
> 
> **Q2: UI Split Strategy (Sprint 4)**
> - **Decision**: Phased approach. State remains unified in `PaintApp`, and UI panel rendering functions will be moved into `src/ui/` modules (e.g., `menu.rs`, `quick_bar.rs`), passing `&mut PaintApp` directly to simplify borrow check handling and minimize refactoring risk.
> 
> **Q3: Sprint Priority**
> - **Decision**: Sprint 3 (Transform & Selection Polish) will be tackled first to address the critical user-visible gap, followed by Sprint 4 (UI Split) as the organizational refactor.
> 
> **Q4: Release Scope**
> - **Decision**: Keep the proposed Alpha 1 release targets (focusing on Sprints 3, 5, 7, 11, 12) and defer Sprints 6 (Layer Masks), 8 (Reference Images), 9 (Symmetry/Artist Tools), and 10 (ORA Format) to Beta 1.
> 
> **Q5: Transform Handles Visual Style**
> - **Decision**: Standard Transform Gizmo. Draw 8 square handles around the bounding box, a center pivot handle for translation, and an offset rotation handle above the top-center handle, with numeric Pos/Scale/Rot readouts.
> 
> **Q6: Selection Modifiers UI Location**
> - **Decision**: Both. A floating contextual toolbar under the selection for quick commands (Grow/Shrink/Invert/Deselect/Feather), and detailed settings in the Tool Options sidebar.
